476
00:39:19,213 --> 00:39:20,202
Aren't you clever!

477
00:39:20,413 --> 00:39:25,282
That means, "Çome to my Basha.
I'll give you coconut shells."

478
00:39:25,493 --> 00:39:29,884
The natives believe
coconut shells ward off the snakes.

479
00:39:30,093 --> 00:39:32,402
Africa must be fascinating.

480
00:39:32,613 --> 00:39:37,733
A girl like I almost never gets
to meet a really interesting man.

481
00:39:37,933 --> 00:39:41,846
- Sometimes my brain gets starved.
- Poor little thing.

482
00:39:42,173 --> 00:39:46,689
It's a terrible thing to be Ionesome,
especially in the middle of a crowd.

483
00:39:46,933 --> 00:39:48,286
Do you know what I mean?

484
00:39:48,493 --> 00:39:50,768
You'll never be Ionesome again.
Leave it to Piggie.

485
00:39:50,933 --> 00:39:52,412
[DOOR OPENS]

486
00:39:52,573 --> 00:39:57,328
- I've got to see Lorelei alone.
- Shall I wait in the next room?

487
00:39:57,533 --> 00:40:01,367
If you like. We're expecting
Lady Beekman for tea.

488
00:40:01,573 --> 00:40:04,804
Here? I just remembered,
I have another appointment.

489
00:40:05,013 --> 00:40:09,564
I better pop off. Toodle-Ioo,
chin-chin and all that rot.

490
00:40:10,613 --> 00:40:14,367
- That was mean!
- Shut up and listen to me.

491
00:40:14,613 --> 00:40:16,683
- You're in a jam.
- Me? Why?

492
00:40:16,933 --> 00:40:20,209
What were you doing before
Piggie started barking?

493
00:40:20,413 --> 00:40:24,486
- He wasn't barking, that's Swahili.
- Before that.

494
00:40:24,693 --> 00:40:29,403
Were you doing anything you
wouldn't want Mr. Esmond to see?

495
00:40:29,613 --> 00:40:34,528
- Why, no... My goodness, yes!
- What?

496
00:40:34,733 --> 00:40:39,124
He was telling me about South Africa.
It's dangerous.

497
00:40:39,333 --> 00:40:45,966
Full of snakes called pythons.
It seems a python can grab a goat...

498
00:40:46,173 --> 00:40:49,688
...and kill it
by squeezing it to death.

499
00:40:49,893 --> 00:40:52,487
- Get to the point.
- That's all.

500
00:40:52,693 --> 00:40:55,412
What's incriminating about that?

501
00:40:55,573 --> 00:41:00,010
Well, Piggie was being the python,
and I was a goat.

502
00:41:00,253 --> 00:41:01,845
Oh, Lorelei!

503
00:41:02,053 --> 00:41:05,443
Don't worry!
Piggie won't tell anyone!

504
00:41:05,973 --> 00:41:10,364
He won't have to.
When Piggie was squeezing the goat...

505
00:41:10,573 --> 00:41:14,805
...Mr. Malone was taking pictures
through that porthole.

506
00:41:15,013 --> 00:41:19,768
- Whatever for?
- The Natîonal Geographîc magazine.

507
00:41:19,973 --> 00:41:24,125
Wake up, honey.
Mr. Malone has foxed us.

508
00:41:24,333 --> 00:41:27,370
He's been shining up to me
to watch you.

509
00:41:27,573 --> 00:41:32,567
I'll bet you anything he's a private
detective hired by Mr. Esmond.

510
00:41:33,293 --> 00:41:38,208
Gus is jealous without pictures. He sees
that, he'll be absolutely unreasonable.

511
00:41:38,453 --> 00:41:40,808
Yes, he will.

512
00:41:42,093 --> 00:41:44,812
I was gonna kill him,
but I thought better.

513
00:41:45,053 --> 00:41:46,611
Better?

514
00:41:46,813 --> 00:41:49,964
We'll get the photos
if he doesn't know we know.

515
00:41:50,173 --> 00:41:52,767
- I'll get them. He's a man, isn't he?
- How?

516
00:41:52,973 --> 00:41:56,932
Çharm won't work.
He's too smart for that.

517
00:41:57,133 --> 00:42:01,411
- And he was such a doll last night.
- Oh, Dorothy!

518
00:42:01,613 --> 00:42:05,162
Boy, will I tell him off
once we get the pictures!

519
00:42:05,373 --> 00:42:09,252
- The question is, how do we do that?
- Well...

520
00:42:09,853 --> 00:42:15,166
The simplest way is to swipe them. We'll
get our warpaint on and go to work.

521
00:42:53,693 --> 00:42:57,811
- Where's Lorelei tonight?
- You sound interested.

522
00:42:58,013 --> 00:43:01,050
I am, but not in her.

523
00:43:01,253 --> 00:43:06,008
If you are interested,
I know where we could find her.

524
00:43:06,253 --> 00:43:07,891
Just asking a question.

525
00:43:28,373 --> 00:43:30,728
That's all.

526
00:43:56,973 --> 00:43:58,167
Hello.

527
00:43:58,333 --> 00:44:02,963
Mr. Spofford, please give me a hand.
I'm sort of stuck.

528
00:44:03,173 --> 00:44:05,926
- Are you a burglar?
- Heavens, no!

529
00:44:06,133 --> 00:44:08,727
I got locked in.
I was waiting for a friend.

530
00:44:08,933 --> 00:44:13,211
- Why didn't you ring for him?
- I didn't think of it.

531
00:44:13,413 --> 00:44:18,726
- Lf you're a burglar and I help you...
- Please, help before someone comes.

532
00:44:18,933 --> 00:44:23,802
I'm thinking. All right.
I'll help you for two reasons.

533
00:44:24,053 --> 00:44:26,089
Never mind the reasons.

534
00:44:26,293 --> 00:44:29,763
The first is, I'm too young
to be sent to jail.

535
00:44:29,973 --> 00:44:34,603
The second is, you've got
a lot of animal magnetism.

536
00:44:36,853 --> 00:44:39,970
Look, someone's coming.

537
00:44:42,293 --> 00:44:47,572
- What'll I do?
- Hold this around your neck, tight.

538
00:44:54,933 --> 00:44:56,127
Good evening.

539
00:44:56,333 --> 00:45:00,406
I say, whatever are you
doing up there?

540
00:45:00,653 --> 00:45:03,213
I wanted to see the view from here.

541
00:45:03,453 --> 00:45:06,650
Are you feeling well, my dear?

542
00:45:06,853 --> 00:45:10,812
Yes, thank you ever so.
But I must have caught a chill.

543
00:45:11,053 --> 00:45:14,807
- What say we get a spot of sherry?
- I can't.

544
00:45:15,013 --> 00:45:18,972
- Sherry's the best thing for a cold.
- I couldn't.

545
00:45:19,173 --> 00:45:21,926
You do look flushed.
Let me feel your pulse.

546
00:45:22,133 --> 00:45:23,885
No, no, please...

547
00:45:24,093 --> 00:45:28,245
No cause for alarm, my dear.
It's purely medical.

548
00:45:28,453 --> 00:45:32,810
- There's no fever, at any rate.
- I'm all right, I'm fine.

549
00:45:33,013 --> 00:45:35,607
- Such a little hand.
- Put that back.

550
00:45:35,813 --> 00:45:40,933
So sweet, so tiny,
and yet it can hold a human heart.

551
00:45:41,133 --> 00:45:43,363
SPOFFORD: Stop that!
- Beg your pardon?

552
00:45:43,573 --> 00:45:46,531
Well l... Why...

553
00:45:46,693 --> 00:45:49,366
- Laryngitis, I guess.
- No doubt.

554
00:45:49,613 --> 00:45:54,528
- I need sherry. Will you get it?
- I fly on the wings of Mercury.

555
00:45:54,733 --> 00:45:58,692
SPOFFORD: Just hurry up.
- All right, my dear.

556
00:46:02,133 --> 00:46:06,843
How can you stand that old wolf?
His intentions aren't honorable.

557
00:46:07,053 --> 00:46:10,568
For heaven's sakes,
get me out of here!

558
00:46:16,053 --> 00:46:18,169
Help me over here.

559
00:46:19,333 --> 00:46:23,611
You're all bruised? Malone's been
here with me the whole time.

560
00:46:23,813 --> 00:46:30,002
- Mr. Spofford pulled me too hard.
- Never mind. Did you get the pictures?

561
00:46:30,213 --> 00:46:32,010
- They weren't there.
- Sure?

562
00:46:32,213 --> 00:46:36,491
I looked everywhere.
I even looked in the camera shop.

563
00:46:36,693 --> 00:46:40,971
- Then he's got them in his pockets.
- He must, darn it!

564
00:46:41,213 --> 00:46:45,206
He wouldn't hide them if
he thinks we're buying his act.

565
00:46:45,453 --> 00:46:50,481
Order dinner for three in our cabin
and get some drinks.

566
00:46:50,693 --> 00:46:52,809
We'll be there in 10 minutes.

567
00:46:53,013 --> 00:46:56,801
If we can't empty his pockets,
we're not worthy to be women.

568
00:46:57,013 --> 00:46:58,890
I'll have everything ready.

569
00:47:10,773 --> 00:47:14,288
He'll be here in a minute.
Are the drinks ready?

570
00:47:14,493 --> 00:47:16,006
Almost ready.

571
00:47:16,213 --> 00:47:19,728
This room's like an oven.
Let's turn the heat off.

572
00:47:19,933 --> 00:47:21,889
Leave it alone.

573
00:47:22,093 --> 00:47:24,209
But it's hot, why don't...

574
00:47:24,413 --> 00:47:28,804
Oh, for him. You know,
sometimes your brain amazes me.

575
00:47:29,013 --> 00:47:34,406
Thank you. Our drink is water and
bitters, so don't make any remarks.

576
00:47:34,653 --> 00:47:36,211
What are you doing?

577
00:47:36,453 --> 00:47:40,002
This is his.
Are three sleeping pills enough?

578
00:47:40,253 --> 00:47:43,131
Three's a lot. That's potent stuff.

579
00:47:43,333 --> 00:47:46,245
If a thing's worth doing,
it's worth doing well.

580
00:47:46,413 --> 00:47:47,732
[KNOÇKING]

581
00:47:47,893 --> 00:47:49,849
Here we go.

582
00:47:52,613 --> 00:47:55,252
- Çome in.
- Here are your cigarettes.

583
00:47:55,453 --> 00:47:59,128
- Hi, Miss Lee.
- I got cocktails all ready.

584
00:47:59,333 --> 00:48:03,849
- Make yourself at home.
- It's hot in here. Must be 110.

585
00:48:04,053 --> 00:48:06,567
She's afraid of catching cold.

586
00:48:06,813 --> 00:48:10,601
Touch of laryngitis.
Here, specialty of the house.

587
00:48:10,853 --> 00:48:16,007
- That's quite a cocktail.
- It's very mild. Let's drink a toast:

588
00:48:16,213 --> 00:48:20,252
There was a fellow named Sîdney
Who drank tîll he ruîned a kîdney

589
00:48:20,453 --> 00:48:23,843
It shrîveled and shrank
But he drank and he drank

590
00:48:24,053 --> 00:48:26,328
He had fun doîng ît, dîdn 't he?

591
00:48:26,533 --> 00:48:30,526
- Appetizing.
- I know another. Bottoms up.

592
00:48:40,013 --> 00:48:42,004
He looks like he'll explode.

593
00:48:42,453 --> 00:48:47,811
- What are you made of? What was that?
- Scotch, vodka, brandy and gin.

594
00:48:48,053 --> 00:48:50,169
Here, try this.

595
00:48:55,333 --> 00:48:58,166
- That wasn't water!
- No, straight vodka.

596
00:48:58,413 --> 00:49:02,406
Want some more? What's the matter?
Don't you feel well?

597
00:49:02,613 --> 00:49:05,810
- I'm burning up.
- Let's take off your coat.

598
00:49:06,053 --> 00:49:10,171
Yes, you'll feel better.
You'll cool off. I'll help.

599
00:49:10,373 --> 00:49:14,366
Now you just sit down there.
Excuse me a minute.

600
00:49:15,693 --> 00:49:18,924
- Any luck?
- Not so far.

601
00:49:19,133 --> 00:49:22,409
Be sure you check the inside pocket.

602
00:49:22,653 --> 00:49:26,487
- It's not in here.
- It's not in his coat.

603
00:49:26,693 --> 00:49:29,969
There's one other place
it could be: His pants.

604
00:49:30,173 --> 00:49:32,926
- We'll have to get them.
- Should I do it alone?

605
00:49:33,133 --> 00:49:36,170
- Two heads are better than one.
- I suppose so.

606
00:49:36,413 --> 00:49:39,849
It's ticklish business.
We'll stick together.

607
00:49:41,053 --> 00:49:44,966
I nearly went to sleep.
Çould you turn the heat down?

608
00:49:45,173 --> 00:49:48,210
- He needs a glass of water.
- Yes, indeed.

609
00:49:48,413 --> 00:49:50,768
I'd like water, but it's this heat...

610
00:49:51,013 --> 00:49:52,924
Nice glass of water.

611
00:49:53,133 --> 00:49:54,805
Look out!

612
00:49:55,973 --> 00:50:00,012
- Your pants are soaked!
- We can't leave him in wet pants.

613
00:50:00,253 --> 00:50:03,882
- I'll put them under the hair dryer.
- I'll go and change.

614
00:50:04,093 --> 00:50:07,403
- Don't be silly. You'll catch cold.
- No, no! Look...

615
00:50:07,653 --> 00:50:11,407
I won't catch cold!
What kind of a party is this?

616
00:50:13,013 --> 00:50:14,332
[SPEAKS IN FRENÇH]

617
00:50:14,533 --> 00:50:17,331
You're just in time.
Get something to put on him.

618
00:50:17,533 --> 00:50:21,685
Mr. Malone doesn't feel well.
You better go and lie down.

619
00:50:21,893 --> 00:50:26,762
- I feel like lying down for a month.
- Here, put this on.

620
00:50:27,373 --> 00:50:28,931
François'll help.

621
00:50:29,133 --> 00:50:34,161
It's not fair. Two against one,
take a man's pants...

622
00:50:39,893 --> 00:50:43,010
- I don't think it's here.
- It must be.

623
00:50:44,973 --> 00:50:47,567
LORELEl: I've got it! I've got it!

624
00:50:48,653 --> 00:50:53,124
Here. $2.20.
Your negatives and positive prints.

625
00:50:53,333 --> 00:50:57,963
And may I say, in the words
of my countrymen, "Ooh, la, la!"

626
00:50:58,173 --> 00:51:00,562
- Thank you ever so.
- A pleasure.

627
00:51:00,773 --> 00:51:02,172
Hi. Remember me?

628
00:51:02,413 --> 00:51:05,211
Yes. You're one of
the Olympic athletes.

629
00:51:05,413 --> 00:51:08,166
I'm the only 4-letter man on the team.

630
00:51:08,373 --> 00:51:13,163
You should be ashamed to admit it.
No, don't say another word.

631
00:51:15,253 --> 00:51:21,249
This is the most contemptible bit
of impudence I've ever encountered.

632
00:51:21,453 --> 00:51:27,005
Photographing innocent people!
It's invasion of privacy.

633
00:51:27,213 --> 00:51:32,765
If a newspaper got it, your wife
wouldn't know you were being a snake.

634
00:51:32,973 --> 00:51:38,001
I think I better sit down.
Are you sure there are no more?

635
00:51:38,253 --> 00:51:41,006
Positive, Piggie. Do you feel better?

636
00:51:41,213 --> 00:51:44,011
You little angel,
you don't even know that...

637
00:51:44,213 --> 00:51:48,001
...a certain type of girl would
take advantage of this.

638
00:51:48,253 --> 00:51:51,404
She'd have to be
a terrible girl to be mean...

639
00:51:51,653 --> 00:51:55,089
...to a sweet, intelligent,
generous man like you.

640
00:51:55,373 --> 00:51:59,446
My dear, let me do something
to show my gratitude.

641
00:51:59,733 --> 00:52:04,204
- Thank you ever so!
- May I kiss your hand?

642
00:52:04,453 --> 00:52:09,846
A kiss on the hand feels good,
but a diamond tiara lasts forever.

643
00:52:10,053 --> 00:52:12,726
- Tiara?
- Lady Beekman's. I'd love it.

644
00:52:12,933 --> 00:52:15,606
- Good gracious.
- What's the matter?

645
00:52:15,853 --> 00:52:20,483
Wouldn't you rather have
some furs or a race horse?

646
00:52:20,693 --> 00:52:21,682
No, thank you.

647
00:52:21,893 --> 00:52:26,409
It would be hard to explain
that I'd given it away.

648
00:52:26,613 --> 00:52:30,322
You're so clever.
You could, if you put your mind to it.

649
00:52:30,533 --> 00:52:32,967
- Do you think so?
- Of course.

650
00:52:33,173 --> 00:52:39,203
Besides, it's only fair I should have
her tiara. After all, she has you.

651
00:52:39,413 --> 00:52:42,132
My dear, my very dear!

652
00:52:42,333 --> 00:52:46,770
- Let's get it now.
- Anything you say, my dear.

653
00:52:59,693 --> 00:53:02,332
- Keep an eye on the door.
- Oui, monsieur.

654
00:53:18,053 --> 00:53:21,932
All right, Pierre.
Take this thing back to my cabin.

655
00:53:22,133 --> 00:53:27,969
I'll stay here.
Here's the microphone and a dividend.

656
00:53:28,173 --> 00:53:30,129
Merci, monsieur.

657
00:53:31,253 --> 00:53:34,006
- And leave the door open.
- Oui, monsieur.

658
00:53:36,813 --> 00:53:40,647
Lorelei, they're coming...
How did you get in?

659
00:53:41,173 --> 00:53:44,722
- Through the door.
- Still snooping around?

660
00:53:44,933 --> 00:53:48,403
Nothing to do with you.
I'm paid to watch the blonde...

661
00:53:48,613 --> 00:53:51,002
I'd sure hate to have your job.

662
00:53:51,253 --> 00:53:56,611
Çhecking up on people is messy work,
but only when they're doing things...

663
00:53:56,853 --> 00:54:00,641
Like pretending to make love to a girl
while you spy on her friend?

664
00:54:00,853 --> 00:54:03,572
That part of it is not true.

665
00:54:03,773 --> 00:54:09,530
I don't believe anything you say.
Go away, Sherlock, you're a wrong guy.

666
00:54:09,733 --> 00:54:13,612
- I'm not wrong about you.
- You're only making it worse.

667
00:54:13,853 --> 00:54:16,413
Don't listen, but I'm telling you...

668
00:54:16,653 --> 00:54:20,362
Çome on in,
you can hear better in here.

669
00:54:21,013 --> 00:54:24,130
Am I intruding, or is he leaving?

670
00:54:24,333 --> 00:54:29,566
I'm leaving. But, Miss Lee,
before I go, I'll tell you this.

671
00:54:29,773 --> 00:54:34,324
Sometimes even a mercenary nitwit
like you has a decent impulse.

672
00:54:34,533 --> 00:54:37,843
Don't get your friend mixed up
in your schemes.

673
00:54:38,053 --> 00:54:43,286
Because I'll rub your nose in them,
and I don't want her to get hurt.

674
00:54:43,493 --> 00:54:46,883
If you've nothing more to say,
pray, scat!

675
00:54:47,093 --> 00:54:49,402
That's about all.

676
00:54:49,613 --> 00:54:54,368
Honey, except for telling you
I have money, which I haven't...

677
00:54:54,573 --> 00:55:00,569
...everything else I said, I meant.
And it wasn't part of my job either.

678
00:55:02,533 --> 00:55:04,603
Think about it.

679
00:55:08,853 --> 00:55:12,402
Why did you just stand there
and let him kiss you?

680
00:55:12,653 --> 00:55:17,169
It's crazy, but I think
I'm falling in love with that slob.

681
